The paper deals with a problem in computer security, specifically cross-platform binary code similarity detection, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The proposed approach involves the use of neural networks for graph embedding, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the practical applications of the proposed approach, such as plagiarism detection and vulnerability search, which fall under the categories of cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) respectively. Finally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence and falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
